n$s=3/2$ cases is analogous to that observed in our previous work for the\n$s=1/2$ case at a value $\\kappa_{c}=0.80 \\pm 0.01$. However, for the higher\nspin values the transition is of continuous (second-order) type, as in the\nclassical case, whereas for the $s=1/2$ case it appears to be weakly\nfirst-order in nature (although a second-order transition could not be\nexcluded).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Nov 2011 17:06:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-03-01"}
