fected by star formation. Besides, we\nsee a tight correlation between CO(3-2)/(1-0) ratios in the spiral arms and\nstar formation rate surface densities derived from Spitzer 8 {\\mu}m dust flux\ndensities. We also compare the CO(3-2)/(1-0) ratio and the star formation rate\nat different positions within the spiral arms; both are found to decrease as\nthe radius from the nucleus increases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Dec 2011 08:50:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-03"}
